The continuation of TATARA ironmaking is indeed a remarkable preservation of traditional craftsmanship. The transition from Akira Kihara to Kaoru Horio underscores the depth and resilience of this centuries-old tradition. It's fascinating how such ancient techniques continue to inform modern manufacturing practices, as seen in Proterial's commitment to maintaining the Nittoho Tatara operation.

The principles underlying TATARA ironmaking offer a unique perspective on sustainable and artisanal approaches to production, which can be invaluable in today